Jeanette Chabalala and James de Villiers, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Meekahaefele Masooa who is accused of killing 39-year-old Douglas Pearce in an apparent road rage incident, is expected to return to the South Gauteng High Court on Wednesday.&nbsp;Pearce was killed on Malibongwe Drive, Johannesburg, on February 14, 2014.At Masooa&rsquo;s previous appearance on Friday, the court heard Pearce died within five minutes after he was shot.&nbsp;Pearce was on his motorbike when he became involved in an argument with Masooa. Both men pulled over and continued their confrontation, the court heard.&nbsp;During Masooa's bail application in 2014, it emerged that both men carried firearms. Mosooa claims he acted in self-defence after Pearce confronted him."He shouted at me, pointed the middle finger at me. I don't know why he did that," he said at the time. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.